018-10-12T23:47:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/429491401","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> Is overflow: hidden; needed after this PR?\r\n\r\nThis turned out to be quite an interesting question. as my initial expectation was that it wouldn't be needed, but my gut said leave it just in case there's some edge case. \r\n\r\nlong story short: It's still needed for edge cases.\r\n\r\nRealistically, `height: 100%` (and width) should be all that's needed, _but_ there are are a few edges cases that including `overflow: hidden` takes care of. One such edge case is this picture:\r\n\r\n Where a resize event can cause an inactive scrollbar to get 'stuck'\r\n\r\n![image](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/13877593\/46899255-f39cb980-ce45-11e8-928a-38b4916d1dc3.png)\r\n\r\nSo it does appear that there are contrived ways to break the page if you don't include `overflow: hidden`. The easiest way was to just the window size just slightly, immediately after a resize event occurs.\r\n\r\nIt can also cause an odd side effect of \"ghost scrollbars\" that flicker as you shrink the window down. These scrollbars show up momentarily in between resize events. \r\n\r\nSo there are a bunch of dd edge cases that suddenly become an issue if you remove `overflow: hidden`. \r\n\r\n-------\r\n\r\nI also believe because on this page: https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/?q=misc#misc_controls_trackball\r\n\r\nis  in an `iframe`, the overflowing element is clipped by the iframe first, the `body` doesn't have any direct children that overflow, and thus, no overscroll behavior.\r\n\r\nBut I'm not 100% on that last point. Scrolling can be really weird sometimes.","created_at":"2018-10-13T01:01:37.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15042#issuecomment-429498529","id":429498529,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15042","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyOTQ5ODUyOQ==","updated_at":"2018-10-13T01:01:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/429498529","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/13877593?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/XanderLuciano","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzODc3NTkz","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"XanderLuciano","type":"User","id":13877593,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github