tps:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/boulabiar","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTIxMQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"boulabiar","type":"User","id":101211,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/boulabiar\/orgs"}},{"index":13,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@XanderLuciano - you had asked for feedback and testing from iOS users (sorry for the late response, been under a very tight deadline at work recently). I've got a video capture showing behavior of the threejs trackball control ion iOS 12.0.1 in the Safari browser with the latest code changes (including overflow: hidden and box-sizing: border-box).\r\nhttps:\/\/youtu.be\/2a5jGpH1Gzo\r\n\r\nFrame rate doesn't drop off, but you can see that it still tries to overscroll. And you can see that it really doesn't behave well with the zoom events. Cleanest way to resolve all of this in iOS\/Safari is to simply attach the trackball controls to the div for the renderer rather than letting it attach to the document.\r\n","created_at":"2018-10-20T20:42:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15042#issuecomment-431616518","id":431616518,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15042","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMTYxNjUxOA==","updated_at":"2018-10-20T20:42:34.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/431616518","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/43352196?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mholladay","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzMzUyMTk2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mholladay","type":"User","id":43352196,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/orgs"}},{"index":14,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@mholladay Thank you! Looks like I've only managed to solve one piece of puzzle with this bug, but your video highlights the secondary issue quite well.\r\n\r\nAfter some digging it appears this is a \"feature\" apple added to safari to improve accessibility by ignoring the `user-scalable=no` meta tag.\r\n\r\n\r\n> Cleanest way to resolve all of this in iOS\/Safari is to simply attach the trackball controls to the div for the renderer rather than letting it attach to the document.\r\n\r\nIn this scenario is calling `preventDefault()` or `stopPropagation()` required as well? (From my initial research it would appear so).\r\n\r\nSeems like I might need to go find an iPhone to borrow in order to properly figure out the ideal solution. Seems there are some potential drawbacks with some solutions such as breaking scrolling completely. \r\n\r\nI did find [one promising solution on stack overflow](https:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/37808180\/disable-viewport-zooming-ios-10-safari) though:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nwindow.addEventListener(\r\n    \"touchmove\",\r\n    function(event) {\r\n        if (event.scale !== 1) {\r\n            event.preventDefault();\r\n        }\r\n    },\r\n    { passive: false }\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nI know there are some additional CSS methods to try as well, so I'll have to report back with my findings.\r\n\r\nEdit: using css's `touch-action` doesn't seem to be a viable solution due to lack of support in safari specifically. This is further explained in [this comment](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14013#issuecomment-432178319).","created_at":"2018-10-23T09:20:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15042#issuecomment-432167963","id":432167963,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15042","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMjE2Nzk2Mw==","updated_at":"2018-10-23T09:53:57.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/432167963","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/13877593?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/XanderLuciano","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzODc3NTkz","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"XanderLuciano","type":"User","id":13877593,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/XanderLuciano\/orgs"}},{"index":15,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@XanderLuciano Yes, if you attach the controls to the div rather than the document still need to call preventDefault() and stopPropagation(). Specifically passing { passive: false } when adding the event listeners also works (and allows you to attach to the document rather than just the div), but then you have to deal with older versions of browser that don't support that setting.","created_at":"2018-10-24T23:57:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15042#issuecomment-432867226","id":432867226,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15042","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMjg2NzIyNg==","updated_at":"2018-10-24T23:57:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/432867226","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/43352196?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mholladay","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzMzUyMTk2","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mholladay","type":"User","id":43352196,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mholladay\/orgs"}}]}